<title>PAKISTAN: Pakistan restricts lending to Islamic funds.</title>
<headline>Pakistan restricts lending to Islamic funds.</headline>
<dateline>KARACHI, Pakistan 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>The State (central) Bank of Pakistan said on Wednesday it had told banks to get its permission before granting financing facilities to modarabas (Islamic mutual funds). It gave no reason for the move.</p>
<p>The Karachi-based Business Recorder reported on Wednesday that the Corporate Law Authority had allowed two modarabas, D.G. Modaraba and Paramount Modaraba, to wind up business voluntarily and return investors' money through the sale of assets.</p>
<p>Modaraba companies have gone through hard times for the past two years since the government began taxing their profits.</p>
<p>-- Karachi newsroom 9221-5685192</p>
